# panma-harness — Post-Finish Rules (example template)
#
# Read by rule-applier after the universal review/security-review skills run.
# Each rule below is one of:
#
#   - kind: shell   — a deterministic shell command (formatter, --fix linter,
#                     changelog updater, etc.). rule-applier runs it directly.
#                     If `cmd` is destructive across many files, rule-applier
#                     proposes before applying.
#
#   - kind: check   — a free-form check description. rule-applier reads the
#                     diff and reports findings, but does NOT modify code.
#
# Any rule whose `name` appears in .harness/skip-rules.json is skipped silently.

- name: <rule-name-1>
  kind: shell
  cmd: <your-formatter-or-linter-command>
  scope: changed-files-only        # one of: changed-files-only | whole-tree | "<glob>"

- name: <rule-name-2>
  kind: check
  description: <one-line check, e.g. "every new public function has a docstring">

- name: <rule-name-3>
  kind: shell
  cmd: <your-changelog-update-command>
